    <note type="source">Brill's New Pauly: "Phaleas, of Chalcedon. Greek thinker (5th cent.
      or 1st half of the 4th cent. BC) who concerned himself with polis structures but should probably 
      not be regarded as one of the Sophists... Scholars appear keen to attribute to P. an influence on Aristophanes (Eccl. 667-710) and Plato ..as well as a closeness to Protagoras and Hippodamus ..." eppin, Hartmut (Hannover), “Phaleas”, in: Brill’s New Pauly, Antiquity volumes edited by: Hubert Cancik and , Helmuth Schneider. Consulted online on 02 September 2016</note>
